Response ID: resp_3987
Response Text: Women of color only account for 3% of Hollywood's directors. Less than 1% for each specific culture (Black, Latina, Asian, Indigenous, etc.)... I don't think the overwhelming majority of white men who fund and produce our media are racists. I just think they're spending more time with fellas who share their background. I just think they're spending more money on movies that share their point of view. But the thing is--the market is not their mirror. Audiences are diverse, and POC film audiences actually outspend their counterparts on movies and TV via streaming. In January 2025, Forbes Magazine reported that Hollywood is losing an estimation of $10 billion per year over a lack of representation. What if Austin became the top indie filmmaking hub for artists of color? We don't have the connections in LA nor the generational wealth to move there. Money and access are our top barriers--what if Austin offered POC and female filmmakers both? If ACME was intentional with this mission, however coded it may have to be for political purposes--it would be a moneymaker for the city and for its most underserved artists!

